A man is due to appear at the Tonga Magistrate s Court for possession of a rhino horn on Monday.The 21-year-old man appearance comes after police received a tip-off on Friday about a certain man residing within the Tonga area who was in possession of rhino horn.The members swiftly proceeded to the house and searched it but to no avail.It then transpired that an unidentified man was seen running out of the house into the sugar cane field, carrying a plastic bag.The police members chased the suspect on foot and successfully apprehended the suspect, carrying the said plastic bag. Police searched the suspect and upon closely inspecting the contents of the bag, a rhino horn was found.-TNA Reporter 